message.content: The $x$-coordinate of $B$ is $2$ less than the $x$-coordinate of $A$, which is $(9-2)=7$.  The $y$-coordinate of $B$ is $10$ less than the $y$-coordinate of $A$, which is $(3+10)=13$.  So the $x$-coordinate of $B$ is $7$, and the $y$-coordinate of $B$ is $13$.  Thus, the sum of the coordinates of $B$ is $7+13=\boxed{20}$.
